==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whortleberry
<hw>Whor"tle*ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wyrtil</ets> a small shrub (dim. of <ets>wyrt</ets> wort) + E.
<ets>berry</ets>. See <er>Wort</er>, and cf. <er>Huckleberry</er>,
<er>Hurtleberry</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>In
England, the fruit of <spn>Vaccinium Myrtillus</spn>; also, the plant
itself. See <er>Bilberry</er>, 1.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The fruit of
several shrubby plants of the genus <gen>Gaylussacia</gen>; also, any
one of these plants. See <er>Huckleberry</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

